Pivot admin styles tests

Let's considere some styles sets :

/table pivot style sets
[ name     | parents  | custom style                                                |
| main     |          | color='#000000', decimal-separator='.', text-align='center' |
| main2    |          | font-style='italic'                                         |
| decimal  | main     | decimal=2, text-align='right'                               |
| currency | decimal  | unit='$', thousand-separator=' '                            |
| salary   | currency | decimal=0, unit='K$'                                        |

Here is the pivot setup definition :
/table pivot setup
/inline  
[ pivot Id ] employee.statistics.module |

[ available measures ]  """
  ssn@count, 
  salary@sum, 
  salary@percentile90, 
  salary@average/managedOu.ouId, 
  managedOu.teamCount@sum, 
  %salary@sum/managedOu.teamCount@sum """ |

[ available dimensions ] 
  ssn, salary, managedOu.ouId, managedOu.teamCount  |
/endInline 

_Check global styles :
/sequence 
 [ global parent | global custom | global full style ?                                                            | comments                                                                    
 |               |               | thousand-separator='\,', decimal-separator='.'                                 | --> Default hardcoded into DefaultPivotRefiner#getDefaultStyle              
 |               | unit='X'      | unit='X'                                                                       | --> Override default locally                                                
 | main          |               | color='#000000', decimal-separator='.', text-align='center'                    | --> Override default by setting a parent style set                          
 | main          | unit='X'      | unit='X', color='#000000', decimal-separator='.', text-align='center'          | --> Override default by setting a parent style set + adding local attributs 



_Check fields styles wihout any customization

For this first set of tests, the global pivot style is not overrided, that mean that the defaut style is the one hardcoded into *DefaultPivotRefiner#getDefaultStyle()* :
 **decimal-separator='.', thousand-separator='\,'**

 The measure starting with *percent* has also an hardcoded style into *SimplePivotRefinerField#getStyle()* :
 **unit='%'**
 
 The *decimal* measure also an hardcoded style into *SimplePivotRefinerField#getStyle()* :
 **decimal=2**

 The field salary has also an hardcoded style into HRSample's method  *EmployeePivotRefiner.SalaryField#getStyle()* : 
 **unit='K€'**
 
/sequence  
 [ measure                             | cross items style ?                                                  | comments                                                                                                  |
 | ssn@count                           | decimal-separator='.', thousand-separator='\,'                       | --> Default hardcoded DefaultPivotRefiner#getDefaultStyle()                                               |
 | salary@sum                          | decimal-separator='.', thousand-separator='\,', decimal=2, unit='K€' | --> Default hardcoded DefaultPivotRefiner#getDefaultStyle() + EmployeePivotRefiner.SalaryField#getStyle() |
 | salary@percentile90                 | decimal-separator='.', thousand-separator='\,', decimal=2, unit='K€' | --> Default hardcoded DefaultPivotRefiner#getDefaultStyle() + EmployeePivotRefiner.SalaryField#getStyle() |
 | managedOu.teamCount@sum             | decimal-separator='.', thousand-separator='\,'                       | --> Default hardcoded DefaultPivotRefiner#getDefaultStyle()                                               |
 | %salary@sum/managedOu.teamCount@sum | decimal-separator='.', thousand-separator='\,', decimal=2, unit='%'  | --> Default hardcoded DefaultPivotRefiner#getDefaultStyle() + SimplePivotRefinerField#getStyle()          |



_Check field style with customization using custom style

When the global parent is set, the hardcoded default style is no more used. 

/sequence 
 [ measure    | global parent | global custom   | custom     | cross items style ?                                                               | comments                             |
 | ssn@count  |               |                 | unit='SSN' | decimal-separator='.', thousand-separator='\,', unit='SSN'                        | --> Custom + Default hardcoded       |
 | ssn@count  | main          |                 |            | color='#000000', decimal-separator='.', text-align='center'                       | --> Main                             |
 | ssn@count  | main          |                 | unit='SSN' | color='#000000', decimal-separator='.', text-align='center', unit='SSN'           | --> Main + custom                    |
 | ssn@count  | main2         |                 |            | font-style='italic'                                                               | --> Main2                            |
 | ssn@count  | main2         |                 | unit='SSN' | font-style='italic', unit='SSN'                                                   | --> Main2 + custom                   |
 | ssn@count  | main2         | color='#AAAAAA' | unit='SSN' | color='#AAAAAA', font-style='italic', unit='SSN'                                  | --> Main2 overided style + custom    |

 The harcoded custom style is used only if not redifined for field :

 | salary@sum | main          |                 |            | color='#000000', decimal-separator='.', text-align='center', decimal=2, unit='K€' | --> Custom + Default hardcoded       | 


_Check field style with customization using parent style

/sequence 
 [ measure                       | global parent | parents | custom          | cross items style ?                                                                                      | comments                                                                        |
 | salary@sum                    | main          | main    |                 | color='#000000', decimal-separator='.', text-align='center'                                              | --> parent is 'default', then it is exactly as if no parent was set for field ! |
 | salary@percentile90           | main          | salary  |                 | color='#000000', decimal-separator='.', text-align='right', decimal=0, unit='K$', thousand-separator=' ' | --> salary                                                                      |
 | salary@average/managedOu.ouId | main          | salary  | color='#999999' | color='#999999', decimal-separator='.', text-align='right', decimal=0, unit='K$', thousand-separator=' ' | --> salary + custom                                                             |
 | managedOu.teamCount@sum       | main          | main    | decimal=4       | color='#000000', decimal-separator='.', text-align='center', decimal=4                                   | --> main + custom                                                               |

 If the global parent is not set, it means that the global parent is the one hadcoded into *DefaultPivotRefiner#getDefaultStyle()* 
 
/sequence 
 [ measure                       | global parent | parents | custom    | cross items style ?                                                    | comments              |
 | salary@sum                    |               |         |           | decimal-separator='.', thousand-separator='\,', decimal=2, unit='K€'   | --> Default hardcoded |
 | salary@sum                    |               | main    |           | color='#000000', decimal-separator='.', text-align='center'            | --> Main              |
 | salary@sum                    |               | main    | decimal=5 | color='#000000', decimal-separator='.', text-align='center', decimal=5 | --> Main + custom     |

 The global parent is ignored when the field's parent overrides it :
 
/sequence 
 [ measure                       | global parent | global custom   | parents | custom | cross items style ?                                         | comments                                                      |
 | salary@sum                    | main2         |                 |         |        | font-style='italic', decimal=2, unit='K€'                   | --> Main2                                                     |
 | salary@sum                    | main2         |                 | main    |        | color='#000000', decimal-separator='.', text-align='center' | --> Main hides the global Main2                               |
 | salary@sum                    | main2         | color='#FFFFFF' | main    |        | color='#000000', decimal-separator='.', text-align='center' | --> Main hides the global Main2 including Main2 customization |







